title: The guy who voiced Hey Arnold is now a total hot hipster and musician - and he's making everyone swoon
text:

We all remember the classic 90s cartoon Hey Arnold! but how many of us know what the voice actor looked like? 
That lovable football-shaped head had all the cartoon ladies swooning (sort of) - and now the actor behind him is having the same affect. 
His name is Lane Toran and he's a musician now among other things. 
Disappointingly he doesn't have a football-shaped head (or should that be rugby?), but you can't have everything. 
He has quite a lot going for him as it turns out. He's an actor, musician and went on to voice other characters in the Disney universe as well as Jimmy Neutron. 
Just look at him. Total cool musician and hipster. He's winning at life.
